# Your rule content

In this project, we create blog like lessons for users to read through to learn about Next JS,
This is done via MDX files in the content/lessons folders.

When we create a new lesson we should create the lesson in a folder that is the correct category for the lesson.

The lessons should be like a blog post and explain the topic with examples and possibly diagrams for visual learning, we should NOT just put a bunch of dot points in the post.

We should write paragraphs clearly explaining the concepts for the lesson broken down into sections, which would be separated by headings. 

We do not need to include a heading in the lesson because the heading is supplied by another reusable component. 

At the end of every lesson we should include an interactive lesson link using this component 


<InteractiveExercises href="<link to lesson>">

<!-- Content for what the user will be doing goes here -->

</InteractiveExercises>


New lessons must be added to one of the category lists in the constants.ts file with this format

 {
    id: 'server-components',
    title: 'Server Components',
    description: 'Learn how to use server components in Next.js',
    category: categories['Client & Server'],
    difficulty: difficulties['intermediate'],
    order: 1,
    featured: true,
    status: statuses.completed,
    isDisplayed: isDisplayed.true,
  },


Then the new lesson folder that gets created much match the `id` of this object, this is very important. For example in the above object we have server-components if we now name the lesson ssr it will not load. It must match the id exactly.

